2 Data

d <- readMat("fc_given2.mat") # djy, matlab에서 fam, fqm 추가하여만들었다.
ns <- 20 # ns = number of subjects (children)
nz <- 6 # nz = number of knower-level stages
gn <- 15 # gn = maximum give-n response
fnq <- drop(d$fnq) # fnq = number questions for each child on fast cards
fq <- d$fq # fq = matrix of questions asked to each child on fast cards
fa <- d$fa # fa = matrix of answers given by each child on fast cards

wlist <- drop(d$wlist) # 0을 제외한 응답 유형
fn <- drop(d$fn) # 0을 제외한 응답 가짓수
fa <- d$fam # wlist에서 응답 유형 위치, 원래 fa와 다르다. 단순화시킨듯.
fq <- d$fqm # wlist에서 질문 유형 위치, 원래 fq와 같다.

3 MCMC

data <- list('ns','fnq','fn','fa','fq','nz','gn')

# parameters to be monitored:
parameters <- c('predfa','predz','predfpi','v','z')

# model
model_text <- "
# Knower Level Model Applied to Fast-Cards Data
model {
  # Data
  for (i in 1:ns){
    for (j in 1:fnq[i]){  
      # Probability a z[i]-Knower Will Give fa[i,j] when Asked for fq[i,j]
      fa[i,j] ~ dcat(fnpiprime[z[i],fq[i,j],1:fn])
    }
    # Posterior Predictive
    for (j in 1:gn){
      predfa[i,j] ~ dcat(fnpiprime[z[i],j,1:fn])
    }
  }
  # Model
  for (i in 1:nz){
    for (j in 1:gn){
      for (k in 1:fn){
        fpiprimetmp[i,j,k,1] <- fpi[k]
        fpiprimetmp[i,j,k,2] <- 1/v*fpi[k]
        fpiprimetmp[i,j,k,3] <- v*fpi[k]
        # Will be 1 if Knower-Level (i.e, i-1) is Same or Greater than Answer
        find1[i,j,k] <- step((i-1)-k)
        # Will be 1 for the Possible Answer that Matches the Question
        find2[i,j,k] <- equals(k,j)
        # Will be 1 for 0-Knowers
        find3[i,j,k] <- equals(i,1)
        # Will be 1 for HN-Knowers
        find4[i,j,k] <- equals(i,nz)
        find5[i,j,k] <- find3[i,j,k]+find4[i,j,k]*(2+find2[i,j,k])
                        + (1-find4[i,j,k])*(1-find3[i,j,k])
                        * (find1[i,j,k]+find1[i,j,k]*find2[i,j,k]+1)
        fpiprime[i,j,k] <- fpiprimetmp[i,j,k,find5[i,j,k]]
        fnpiprime[i,j,k] <- fpiprime[i,j,k]/sum(fpiprime[i,j,1:fn])
      } 
    }
  }
  # Posterior Prediction For Knower Levels
  for (i in 1:nz){
    for (j in 1:gn){
      predz[i,j] ~ dcat(fnpiprime[i,j,1:fn])
    }
  }      
  # Base rate
  for (i in 1:fn){
    fpitmp[i] ~ dunif(0,1)
    fpi[i] <- fpitmp[i]/sum(fpitmp[1:fn])
  }
  predfpi ~ dcat(fpi[1:fn]) 
  # Priors   
  v ~ dunif(1,1000)
  for (i in 1:ns) {
    z[i] ~ dcat(priorz[])
  }
  for (i in 1:nz){
    priorz[i] <- 1/6
  }      
}
"
samples <- jags(data, parameters.to.save = parameters, 
                model.file = textConnection(model_text), 
                n.chains=4, n.iter=2000, n.burnin=1000, n.thin=1)

getmode <- function(v) {
  uniqv <- unique(v)
  uniqv[which.max(tabulate(match(v, uniqv)))]
}
